&gt;
&gt; It depends on too many things to give a specific answer here but
&gt; as a general rule I would always try to have my runtime release
&gt; code check for the &#39;cleanness&#39; of all connections, even if I had
&gt; to write a specific class with functionality for this.
&gt; I&#39;d then hammer these with unit test cases to make sure they will
&gt; always gurantee clean conncections.
&gt; I&#39;m not very up on JDBC. You may have to wrap JDBC in your own
&gt; shell to provide the integrity checking.
&gt;
&gt; Noboddy should need reminding that whatever it costs, a clean
&gt; database is worth the pain.
&gt;
&gt;
