&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; &gt;For software quality two of the most important things to test for
&gt; &gt;(if you can) are:
&gt; &gt;1. Connections are &#39;clean&#39; when you put them back in the pool.
&gt; &gt;The next piece of code to use the connection should be able to
&gt; &gt;do so without fear of picking up a bad connection or one which
&gt; &gt;wasn&#39;t tidied up properly by the last user.
&gt;
&gt; Just out of interest, (and getting a little OT) is there any way to
&gt; check
&gt; (within the code - not as a unit test) that the connection is &quot;clean&quot; -
&gt; ie
&gt; ResultSets, statements closed etc.?
&gt;
&gt;
